summary: The meeting served as an introduction to "Doggy Shop," a new startup focused on providing a one-stop platform for dog owners to access quality medicines, wellness products, and essential care items, all delivered to their doorstep. The platform's technology stack was detailed, with the front end utilizing React and Next.js for a seamless user experience, and the back end powered by Node.js and Express. Data management is handled by Postgres for structured data and Redis for caching, ensuring high performance. In its initial quarter, Doggy Shop has achieved significant traction, onboarding over a thousand customers and partnering with more than fifty veterinary clinics and certified suppliers. The company is experiencing a 25% month-on-month revenue growth and boasts a customer retention rate of over 70%. For cloud infrastructure, AWS is being used, specifically EC2 for compute and S3 for storage.

topics.summary: Surya Vashisth introduces Doggy Shop, a new startup focused on the health and happiness of dogs. The platform aims to be a one-stop shop for dog parents to access quality medicines, wellness products, and essential care items, all delivered to their doorstep.

Harsh Bansal details the technology used for the Doggy Shop platform. The front end utilizes React and Next.js for a responsive user experience. The back end is powered by Node.js and Express. The database uses Postgres for structured data and Redis for caching to ensure high performance during peak traffic.

Surya Vashisth presents the initial performance of Doggy Shop in its first quarter. This includes onboarding over a thousand customers, partnering with fifty veterinary clinics and suppliers, achieving a 25% month-on-month revenue growth, and maintaining a customer retention rate above 70%.
Harsh Bansal outlines the cloud infrastructure used for Doggy Shop, which is AWS. Specifically, EC2 is used for compute power and S3 for storage.
